{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2ff5ea44-1ca1-4ebd-9d66-547a6419040a","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **dropped support** for:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is out of support; you must upgrade to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`.NET Framework < 4.6.2`** — your `net462` is the minimum, so that's fine.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — .NET Core 3.1 is out of support; you must upgrade to `net6.0`+.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|--------|----------------------|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No — use `net6.0`+ |\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ No — use `net6.0`+ |\n\n### What to do\n\nUpdate your `TargetFrameworks` before migrating. For example:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nWould you like me to perform the full MSTest v2 → v3 migration for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1bf29acb-2d5f-4912-9899-251ce91268e3","outputTokens":278,"requestId":"9C43:A21C3:4B03D73:598AC69:69F86B85"},"id":"273342ec-c94c-4c71-9e16-35e0ef8dddb0","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:49:00.521Z","parentId":"5a88ca04-893f-4ea0-a5d3-ff9b5da71ca6"}
